{
  "texts": [
    "In contrast, Clec11a holds more advantages.",
    "It not only focuses on inhibiting bone resorption but also emphasizes promoting bone formation, promising more stable and long-lasting therapeutic effects.",
    "Furthermore, Clec11a seems to play a specific role in the differentiation of BMSCs into OB without affecting other cell lines differentiated from BMSC (61).",
    "This unique target point suggests that it might reduce adverse reactions similar to those of existing drugs.",
    "Among the current multidrugs, parathyroid hormone (PTH) can effectively regulate bone mass by stimulating bone formation and bone resorption (62)."
  ]
}